title: Tan's Asian Cafe
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Offers many vegan Chinese and Indonesian dishes including crispy mongolian tofu, spicy curry tofu, and balinese tofu. Indonesian vegan appetizers include lentu, tahu isi, and somasas. The staff is helpful and knowledgeable about veganism. It is a small, casual restaurant next to Esposito's Garden Center with both indoor and outdoor seating. During lunch it can be quite busy.  Lunch specials are offered seven days a week and include soup and rice (ask for the hot and sour soup and white rice, if you are vegan).
